description:
System Engineer engineering, information technology SAP, MATLAB, Simulink **Become our next FutureStarter**


** System Engineer**

Country/Region:   CN               Location:     Jiaxing, ZJ, CN, 314000   

Req ID 71444 | Jiaxing, China, ZF Drivetech (Jiaxing) Co., Ltd.


System Qualification Engineer:

Job Requirement:

1. Part of the global system integration team to release new SW-releases for prototyping, vehicle testing and series releases (A-D Level)_  
2. Creation of test plans based on product-related requirement specifications, and optimization of test plans;  
3. Perform basic calibration and testing of all functions for all e-Mobility products;  
4. Define new or customized e-Mobility functionalities, E/E interfaces and diagnostic services with global functional teams;  
5. Support the SW application team in China to bring these basic release to customer releases;  
6. Analyze and evaluate test results, create release documentations and follow all processes required for these tasks;  
7. Commissioning of complex electric drives and electric drive systems including power electronics on the test bench and in the vehicle;  
8. Create knowledge and training experience for all tools and applications in order to hold our own basic training for new employees;  
9. Support the global integration team on testing and analyzing campaigns, like introduction of new valves or sensor ; 

Qualification:

1. Bachelor or above in mechatronics or electrical engineering with at least 3 years of professional experience in calibration or integration, overall systems is plus;  
2. Knowledge and experience in the application of relevant customer and ISO standards in the field of e-mobility;   
3. Experience in handling power electronics and control units as well as analyzing circuit/wiring diagrams;  
4. Good knowledge of MATLAB / Simulink, as well as Vector application tools are advantageous;  
5. Good analytical skills combined with a comprehensive understanding of processes;  
6. High level of assertiveness with moderation and communication skills as well as team capability;   
7. Advanced knowledge of automotive spice processes, especially SYS.4 and SYS.5;  
8. Fluent English both in written and oral.


Be part of our ZF team as System Engineer and apply now!

Contact

Fangyuan Shen

